snippet.textDisplay:
8:08... my god I had something so similar happen to me as a kid. It was probably around 1993 or 1994. My family still had an original NES at home even though the SNES was out for a while. It was Christmas time and I remember asking my dad for the newer "Nintendo". I didn't really know that it was called a "Super Nintendo" since I was probably only 5 or 6 at the time. I just described it as the new "Nintendo" that you load the games in from the top and not from the front.


Little did I know that there was a top load NES version of the console that just came out that same year. My didn't know anything about video games so he figured this was the one I was describing. I mean... I couldn't get mad.. It was new, it loaded games from the top, and it was a Nintendo.

I honestly didn't expect the name of the new Xbox to be this bad. I figured it would just be another subliminal "winning" name, but this is just awful.
There's an upside to how bad this name is though, and that's all the inevitable jokes about "Xbox SE-X" that are sure to be coming.
Xbox fan: "Hey, wanna come over and play some Xbox?"
Friend: "No thanks, I'd rather not play at SE-X with you."
That's just the most obvious one. I'm sure there's gonna be some real gold eventually.
